        <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Is Midjourney or Stable Diffusion better for beginners?</h3>
    <p>Midjourney is significantly easier for beginners. You describe your vision in natural language and receive beautiful images without any technical setup. Stable Diffusion requires understanding model selection, prompt engineering, and often local GPU hardware.</p>
    <h3>Which AI image generator gives more control over the output?</h3>
    <p>Stable Diffusion offers vastly more control through LoRA models for subject-specific training, ControlNet for pose and composition guidance, and IP-Adapter for style transfer. Midjourney's control is limited to prompt parameters and aspect ratio.</p>
    <h3>Can Stable Diffusion run on my computer without paying?</h3>
    <p>Yes, Stable Diffusion is free and open source. You need a compatible GPU (NVIDIA RTX 2060 or better recommended). Midjourney requires a monthly subscription starting at $10 and runs on their cloud servers.</p>
    <h3>Which tool is better for commercial projects?</h3>
    <p>Both support commercial use. Midjourney's paid plans include commercial usage rights. Stable Diffusion's open-source license permits commercial use, but specific model licenses on platforms like CivitAI may vary.</p>
